  "prompt": "My friend block a person on what's app how could I know really he is blocked?",
  "response": "If your friend has blocked someone on WhatsApp, there are several indicators that can help you determine if this is the case:\n\n1. **No Profile Updates**: Typically, if someone is blocked, you might not be able to see their profile picture, status updates, or last seen timestamp.\n\n2. **Message Delivery**: When messaging a person who has blocked you, the messages you send will only show one check mark (sent) and not the second check mark (delivered).\n\n3. **Calls**: Attempting to make a voice or video call to someone who has blocked you will not go through.\n\n4. **Group Chats**: If both users are in the same group chat, messages will appear as usual. However, replies and other interactions between the blocked user and the blocker will garner no direct response.\n\n5. **Online Status**: The \"Online\" status or \"Last Seen\" may no longer be visible if you are blocked.\n\nPlease note that these indicators can also be signs of other issues like privacy settings or network problems. Blocking on WhatsApp is designed to be private, so these methods are not definitive and can sometimes vary in their accuracy.",
